The paper discusses the challenges of creating AI solutions in government environments where data cannot be freely shared across different agencies, which falls under the domain of AI (cs.AI). The paper also mentions regulatory restrictions and the need for technologies to work around these challenges, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper presents results on building AI models using federated AI, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and could also be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
